00:03:37.220 --> 00:03:39.010
And we also have
some announcements

00:03:39.010 --> 00:03:40.720
for Fused Location Provider.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:42.670
As you know, Fused
Location Provider

00:03:42.670 --> 00:03:45.390
can combine
information using GPS,

00:03:45.390 --> 00:03:49.970
cell tower, and Wi-Fi signals to
accurately determine position.

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:52.130
In this release, we
have greatly improved

00:03:52.130 --> 00:03:54.470
how Fused Location
Provider detects location

00:03:54.470 --> 00:03:55.830
from cell towers.

00:03:55.830 --> 00:03:59.430
Before, location was retrieved
using only the primary cell

00:03:59.430 --> 00:03:59.930
tower.

00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:04.170
But now, Fused Location Provider
also uses other towers nearby

00:04:04.170 --> 00:04:07.000
to provide accurate location.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:10.290
And we've also improved location
detection from Wi-Fi access

00:04:10.290 --> 00:04:14.350
points, particularly in areas
where GPS is not available,

00:04:14.350 --> 00:04:16.240
such as indoors.

00:04:16.240 --> 00:04:17.980
And you get even more
with this release,

00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:20.680
because we have also
important announcements

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:22.850
for the Nearby API.

00:04:22.850 --> 00:04:25.790
Remember the Nearby Publish
Subscribe Architecture

00:04:25.790 --> 00:04:29.980
which allows your app to detect
and retrieve data from beacons?

00:04:29.980 --> 00:04:32.820
Well, in this release we've
enhanced this capability

00:04:32.820 --> 00:04:36.150
so your app does not have
to be in the foreground

00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:37.640
to detect a beacon.

00:04:37.640 --> 00:04:40.650
You can now get notified
when a beacon is nearby,

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:43.260
even when your app
is in the background.

00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:47.080
Check out the release blog
post for more information.

